obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4651)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4651&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board of India Act, 1992.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 30th day of January, 1992.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4652)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4652&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Securities and Exchange Board of India established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairman" means the Chairman of the Board;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) collective investment scheme means any scheme or arrangement which satisfies the`
  line `conditions specified in section 11AA;]`
  line
  line `(c) "existing Securities and Exchange Board" means the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `constituted under the Resolution of the Government of India in the Department of Economic Affairs`
  line `No. 1(44)SE/86, dated the 12th day of April, 1988;`
  line
  line `(d) "Fund" means the Fund constituted under section 14;`
  line
  line `^2[(da) "Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority" means the Insurance Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority of India established under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Insurance`
  line `Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999);`
  line
  line `(db) "Judicial Member" means a Member of the Securities Appellate Tribunal appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 15MA and includes the Presiding Officer.]`
  line
  line `(e) member means a member of the Board and includes the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(f) notification means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `^2[(fa) "Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority" means the Pension Fund`
  line `Regulatory and Development Authority established under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Pension`
  line `Fund Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 2013 (23 of 2013);]`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Board under this Act;`
  line
  line `^3[(ha) Reserve Bank means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);]`
  line
  line `(i) "securities" has the meaning assigned to it in section 2 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation)`
  line `Act, 1956 (42 of 1956).`
  line
  line `^2[(j) "Technical Member" means a Technical Member appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 15 MB.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in ^5[the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) or the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996)] shall have the meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them in that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 11 (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 146 (w.e.f. 26-4-2017).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 2 (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 2, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 22 of 1996, s. 30 and the Schedule, for the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956)`
  line `(w.e.f. 20-9-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4653)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4653&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint, there shall be established, for the purposes of this Act, a Board`
  line `by the name of the Securities and Exchange Board of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract, and shall, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Board shall be at Bombay.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may establish offices at other places in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4654)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Management of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4654&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman;`
  line
  line `(b) two members from amongst the officials of the ^1[Ministry] of the Central Government dealing`
  line `with Finance ^2[and administration of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)];`
  line
  line `(c) one member from amongst the officials of ^3[the Reserve Bank];`
  line
  line `^4[(d) five other members of whom at least three shall be the whole-time members,]`
  line
  line `to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The general superintendence, direction and management of the affairs of the Board shall vest in a`
  line `Board of members, which may exercise all powers and do all acts and things which may be exercised or`
  line `done by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise determined by regulations, the Chairmen shall also have powers of general`
  line `superintendence and direction of the affairs of the Board and may also exercise all powers and do all acts`
  line `and things which may be exercised or done by that Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairman and members referred to in clauses (a) and (d) of sub-section (1) shall be appointed`
  line `by the Central Government and the members referred to in clauses (b) and (c) of that sub-section shall be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government and the ^5[Reserve Bank] respectively.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairman and the other members referred to in clauses (a) and (d) of sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `persons of ability, integrity and standing who have shown capacity in dealing with problems relating to`
  line `securities market or have special knowledge or experience of law, finance, economics, accountancy,`
  line `administration or in any other discipline which, in the opinion of the Central Government, shall be useful`
  line `to the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 3, for "Ministries" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "and Law" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934`
  line `(2 of 1934)" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Reserve Bank of India" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4655)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of Chairman and members of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4655&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `term of office and other conditions of service of the Chairman and the members referred to in clause (d)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 4 shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government shall have the`
  line `right to terminate the services of the Chairman or a member appointed under clause (d) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 4, at any time before the expiry of the period prescribed under sub-section (1), by giving him`
  line `notice of not less than three months in writing or three months salary and allowances in lieu thereof, and`
  line `the Chairman or a member, as the case may be, shall also have the right to relinquish his office, at any`
  line `time before the expiry of the period prescribed under sub-section (1), by giving to the Central`
  line `Government notice of not less than three months in writing.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4656)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Removal of member from office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4656&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1*** The Central Government shall remove a member from`
  line `office if he`
  line
  line `(a) is, or at any time has been, adjudicated as insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves a`
  line `moral turpitude;`
  line
  line ^2*****
  line
  line `(e) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, so abused his position as to render his`
  line `continuation in office detrimental to the public interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that no member shall be removed under this clause unless he has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets and figure "(1)" omitted by Act 9 of 1995, s. 3 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `11. Clause (d) omitted by Act 9 of 1995, s. 3 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4657)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4657&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such times and places, and shall observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including quorum at such meetings) as`
  line `may be provided by regulation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman or, if for any reason, he is unable to attend a meeting of the Board, any other`
  line `member chosen by the members present from amongst themselves at the meeting shall preside at the`
  line meeting.
  line
  line `(3) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Board shall be decided by a majority`
  line `votes of the members present and voting, and, in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairman, or in his`
  line `absence, the person presiding, shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (4658)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title `Member not to participate in meetings in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4658&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Member not to participate in meetings in certain cases.---Any member, who is a director of`
  line `a company and who as such director has any direct or indirect pecuniary interest in any matter coming up`
  line `for consideration at a meeting of the Board, shall, as soon as possible after relevant circumstances have`
  line `come to his knowledge, disclose the nature of his interest at such meeting and such disclosure shall be`
  line `recorded in the proceedings of the Board, and the member shall not take any part in any deliberation or`
  line `decision of the Board with respect to that matter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4659)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4659&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Board`
  line `shall be invalid merely by reason of---`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Board; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Board not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4660)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Officers and employees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4660&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may appoint such other officers and`
  line `employees as it considers necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The term and other conditions of service of officers and employees of the Board appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be such as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (4661)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Transfer of assets, liabilities, etc., of existing Securities and Exchange Board to the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4661&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the date of establishment of the Board,---`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to the existing Securities and Exchange Board in any law other than this Act or`
  line `in any contract or other instrument shall be deemed as a reference to the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) all properties and assets, movable and immovable, of, or belonging to, the existing Securities`
  line `and Exchange Board, shall vest in the Board;`
  line
  line `(c) all rights and liabilities of the existing Securities and Exchange Board shall be transferred to,`
  line `and be the rights and liabilities of, the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) without prejudice to the provisions of clause (c), all debts, obligations and liabilities incurred,`
  line `all contracts entered into and all matters and things engaged to be done by, with or for the existing`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board immediately before that date, for or in connection with the purpose of`
  line `the said existing Board shall be deemed to have been incurred, entered into or engaged to be done by,`
  line `with or for, the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) all sums of money due to the existing Securities and Exchange Board immediately before that`
  line `date shall be deemed to be due to the Board;`
  line
  line `(f) all suits and other legal proceedings instituted or which could have been instituted by or`
  line `against the existing Securities and Exchange Board immediately before that date may be continued or`
  line `may be instituted by or against the Board; and`
  line
  line `(g) every employee holding any office under the existing Securities and Exchange Board`
  line `immediately before that date shall hold his office in the Board by the same tenure and upon the same`
  line `terms and conditions of service as respects remuneration, leave, provident fund, retirement and other`
  line `terminal benefits as he would have held such office if the Board had not been established and shall`
  line `continue to do so as an employee of the Board or until the expiry of the period of six months from`
  line `that date if such employee opts not to be the employee of the Board within such period.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, absorption of any employee by the Board in its regular service under`
  line `this section shall not entitle such employee to any compensation under that Act or other law and no such`
  line `claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other .`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (4662)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4662&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, it shall be the duty of the Board`
  line `to protect the interests of investors in securities and to promote the development of, and to regulate the`
  line `securities market, by such measures as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the measures referred to therein`
  line `may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the business in stock exchanges and any other securities markets;`
  line
  line `(b) registering and regulating the working of stock brokers, sub-brokers, share transfer agents,`
  line `bankers to an issue, trustees of trust deeds, registrars to an issue, merchant bankers, underwriters,`
  line `portfolio managers, investment advisers and such other intermediaries who may be associated with`
  line `securities markets in any manner;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) registering and regulating the working of the ^2[depositories, participants, custodians] of`
  line `securities, foreign institutional investors, credit rating agencies and such other intermediaries as the`
  line `Board may, by notification, specify in this behalf;]`
  line
  line `(c) registering and regulating the working of ^3[venture capital funds and collective investment`
  line `schemes], including mutual funds;`
  line
  line `(d) promoting and regulating self-regulatory organisations;`
  line
  line `(e) prohibiting investors’ education and training of intermediaries of securities markets;`
  line
  line `(f) promoting investors' education and training of intermediaries of securities markets;`
  line
  line `(g) prohibiting insider trading in securities;`
  line
  line `(h) regulating substantial acquisition of shares and take-over of companies;`
  line
  line `(i) calling for information from, undertaking inspection, conducting inquiries and audits of the^4[stock exchanges, mutual funds, other persons associated with the securities market] intermediaries`
  line `and self-regulatory organisations in the securities market;`
  line
  line `^5[(ia) calling for information and records from any person including any bank or any other`
  line `authority or board or corporation established or constituted by or under any Central or State Act`
  line `which, in the opinion of the Board, shall be relevant to any investigation or inquiry by the Board in`
  line `respect of any transaction in securities;]`
  line
  line `^6[(ib) calling for information from, or furnishing information to, other authorities, whether in`
  line `India or outside India, having functions similar to those of the Board, in the matters relating to the`
  line `prevention or detection of violations in respect of securities laws, subject to the provisions of other`
  line `laws for the time being in force in this regard:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board, for the purpose of furnishing any information to any authority outside`
  line `India, may enter into an arrangement or agreement or understanding with such authority with the`
  line `prior approval of the Central Government;]`
  line
  line `(j) performing such functions and exercising such powers under the provisions of ^7*** the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956), as may be delegated to it by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(k) levying fees or other charges for carrying out the purposes of this section;`
  line
  line `(l) conducting research for the above purposes;`
  line
  line `^8[(la) calling from or furnishing to any such agencies, as may be specified by the Board, such`
  line `information as may be considered necessary by it for the efficient discharge of its functions;]`
  line
  line `(m) performing such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^9[(2A) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (2), the Board may take measures`
  line `to undertake inspection of any book, or register, or other document or record of any listed public company`
  line `or a public company (not being intermediaries referred to in section 12) which intends to get its securities`
  line `listed on any recognised stock exchange where the Board has reasonable grounds to believe that such`
  line `company has been indulging in insider trading or fraudulent and unfair trade practices relating to`
  line `securities market.]`
  line
  line `^10[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force while exercising`
  line `exercising the powers under ^11[clause (i) or clause (ia) of sub-section (2) or sub-section (2A)], the Board`
  line `shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of`
  line `1908) while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) the discovery and production of books of account and other documents, at such place and such`
  line `time as may be specified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(ii) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(iii) inspection of any books, registers and other documents of any person referred to in`
  line `section 12, at any place;`
  line
  line `^12[(iv) inspection of any book, or register, or other document or record of the company referred to`
  line `in sub-section (2A);`
  line
  line `(v) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.]`
  line
  line `^12[(4) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-sections (1), (2), (2A) and (3) and`
  line `section 11B, the Board may, by an order, for reasons to be recorded in writing, in the interests of investors`
  line `or securities market, take any of the following measures, either pending investigation or inquiry or on`
  line `completion of such investigation or inquiry, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) suspend the trading of any security in a recognised stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(b) restrain persons from accessing the securities market and prohibit any person associated with`
  line `securities market to buy, sell or deal in securities;`
  line
  line `(c) suspend any office-bearer of any stock exchange or self-regulatory organisation from holding`
  line `such position;`
  line
  line `(d) impound and retain the proceeds or securities in respect of any transaction which is under`
  line investigation;
  line
  line `^13[(e) attach, for a period not exceeding ninety days, bank accounts or other property of any intermediary or any person associated with the securities market in any manner involved in violation of any of the provisions of this Act, or the rules or the regulations made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall, within ninety days of the said attachment, obtain confirmation of the said attachment from the Special Court, established under section 26A, having jurisdiction and on such confirmation, such attachment shall continue during the pendency of the aforesaid proceedings and on conclusion of the said proceedings, the provisions of section 28A shall apply:`
  line
  line `Provided further that only property, bank account or accounts or any transaction entered therein, so far as if related to the proceeds actually involved in violation of any of the provisions of this Act, or the rules or the regulations made thereunder shall be allowed to be attached.]`
  line
  line `(f) direct any intermediary or any person associated with the securities market in any manner not`
  line `to dispose of or alienate an asset forming part of any transaction which is under investigation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board may, without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (2A), take any of the measures specified in clause (d) or clause (e) or clause (f), in respect`
  line `of any listed public company or a public company (not being intermediaries referred to in section 12)`
  line `which intends to get its securities listed on any recognised stock exchange where the Board has`
  line `reasonable grounds to believe that such company has been indulging in insider trading or fraudulent`
  line `and unfair trade practices relating to securities market:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Board shall, either before or after passing such orders, give an`
  line `opportunity of hearing to such intermediaries or persons concerned.`
  line
  line `^14[(4A) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-sections (1), (2), (2A), (3) and (4), section 11B and section`
  line `section 15-I, the Board may, by an order, for reasons to be recorded in writing, levy penalty under sections 15A, 15B, 15C,`
  line `15D, 15E, 15EA, 15EB, 15F, 15G, 15H, 15HA and 15HB after holding an inquiry in the prescribed manner.]`
  line
  line `^15[(5) The amount disgorged, pursuant to a direction issued, under section 11B of this Act or`
  line `section 12A of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) or section 19 of the`
  line `Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996), ^12[or under a settlement made under section 15JB or section 23JA of the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956) or section 19-IA of the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of`
  line `1996)] as the case may be, shall be credited to the Investor Protection and Education Fund established by`
  line `the Board and such amount shall be utilised by the Board in accordance with the regulations made under`
  line `this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 5 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `2 Subs. by Act 22 of 1996, s. 30 and the Schedule, for "depositories, custodians" (w.e.f. 20-9-1995)`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 5, for "collective investment schemes" (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 5,ibid., for "stock exchanges and" (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `2019).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 2, for clause (ia) (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 6-3-1998).`
  line `7. The words, brackets and figures the Capital Issues (Control) Act, 1947 (29 of 1947) and omitted by Act 9 of 1995, s. 5`
  line `(w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 5 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 4, for clause (i) of sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `12 Ins. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 4 (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `13. Subs. by Act 21 of 2019, s. 42 and the Second Schedule, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 21-2-2019).`
  line `14. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 179 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line `15. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 2 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (4663)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 13
  title `Board to regulate or prohibit issue of prospectus, offer document or advertisement soliciting money for issue of securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4663&sectionno=11A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [^2[11A. Board to regulate or prohibit issue of prospectus, offer document or advertisement`
  line `soliciting money for issue of securities.-- (1) Without prejudice to the provisions of the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956), the Board may, for the protection of investors,---`
  line `(a) specify, by regulations--`
  line `(i) the matters relating to issue of capital, transfer of securities and other matters incidental`
  line `thereto; and`
  line `(ii) the manner in which such matters shall be disclosed by the companies;`
  line `(b) by general or special orders---`
  line `(i) prohibit any company from issuing prospectus, any offer document, or advertisement`
  line `soliciting money from the public for the issue of securities;`
  line `(ii) specify the conditions subject to which the prospectus, such offer document or`
  line `advertisement, if not prohibited, may be issued.`
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 21 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act,`
  line `1956 (42 of 1956), the Board may specify the requirements for listing and transfer of securities and other`
  line `matters incidental thereto.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 6 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 5, for section 11A (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_aa:
  sectionId (4664)
  sectionNo 11AA
  orderNo 14
  title `Collective investment scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_aa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_aa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4664&sectionno=11AA&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_11_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[11AA. Collective investment scheme.-- (1) Any scheme or arrangement which satisfies the`
  line `conditions referred to in sub-section (2) ^2[or sub-section (2A)] shall be a collective investment scheme:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that any pooling of funds under any scheme or arrangement, which is not registered with`
  line `the Board or is not covered under sub-section (3), involving a corpus amount of one hundred crore rupees`
  line `or more shall be deemed to be a collective investment scheme.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any scheme or arrangement made or offered by any ^3[person] under which,--`
  line
  line `(i) the contributions, or payments made by the investors, by whatever name called, are pooled and`
  line `utilized for the purposes of the scheme or arrangement;`
  line
  line `(ii) the contributions or payments are made to such scheme or arrangement by the investors`
  line `with a view to receive profits, income, produce or property, whether movable or immovable, from`
  line `such scheme or arrangement;`
  line
  line `(iii) the property, contribution or investment forming part of scheme or arrangement, whether`
  line `identifiable or not, is managed on behalf of the investors;`
  line
  line `(iv) the investors do not have day-to-day control over the management and operation of the`
  line `scheme or arrangement.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) Any scheme or arrangement made or offered by any person satisfying the conditions as may be`
  line `specified in accordance with the regulations made under this Act.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) ^2[or sub-section (2A)], any scheme or`
  line arrangement--
  line
  line `(i) made or offered by a cooperative society registered under the Co-operative Societies Act,`
  line `1912 (2 of 1912) or a society being a society registered or deemed to be registered under any law`
  line `relating to co-operative societies for the time being in force in any State;`
  line
  line `(ii) under which deposits are accepted by non-banking financial companies as defined in`
  line `clause (f) of section 45-I of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(iii) being a contract of insurance to which the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938), applies;`
  line
  line `(iv) providing for any scheme, pension scheme or the insurance scheme framed under the`
  line `Employees Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(v) under which deposits are accepted under section 58A of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(vi) under which deposits are accepted by a company declared as a Nidhi or a Mutual Benefit`
  line `Society under section 620A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(vii) falling within the meaning of chit business as defined in clause (e) of section 2 of the Chit`
  line `Funds Act, 1982 (40 of 1982);`
  line
  line `(viii) under which contributions made are in the nature of subscription to a mutual fund;`
  line
  line `^4[(ix) such other scheme or arrangement which the Central Government may, in consultation with`
  line `the Board, notify,]`
  line
  line `shall not be a collective investment scheme.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_aa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 11 (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  line `2. Ins. by 27 of 2014, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "company" (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013)`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (4665)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to issue directions and levy penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4665&sectionno=11B&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[11B. Power to issue directions ^2[and a levy penalty].-- Save as otherwise provided in section 11, if after making or`
  line `causing to be made an enquiry, the Board is satisfied that it is necessary--`
  line
  line `(i) in the interest of investors, or orderly development of securities market; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to prevent the affairs of any intermediary or other persons referred to in section 12 being`
  line `conducted in a manner detrimental to the interests of investors or securities market; or`
  line
  line `(iii) to secure the proper management of any such intermediary or person,`
  line `it may issue such directions--`
  line
  line `(a) to any person or class of persons referred to in section 12, or associated with the securities`
  line `market; or`
  line
  line `(b) to any company in respect of matters specified in section 11A,`
  line
  line `as may be appropriate in the interests of investors in securities and the securities market.`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power to issue directions`
  line `under this section shall include and always be deemed to have been included the power to direct any`
  line `person, who made profit or averted loss by indulging in any transaction or activity in contravention of the provisions of this Act or regulations made thereunder, to disgorge an amount equivalent to the wrongful`
  line `gain made or loss averted by such contravention.]`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), sub-section (4A) of section 11`
  line `and section 15-I, the Board may, by an order, for reasons to be recorded in writing, levy penalty under`
  line `sections 15A, 15B, 15C, 15D, 15E, 15EA, 15EB, 15F, 15G, 15H, 15HA and 15HB after holding an`
  line `inquiry in the prescribed manner.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 6 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995)`
  line
  line `2.Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 180 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 4 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_c:
  sectionId (4666)
  sectionNo 11C
  orderNo 16
  title Investigation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4666&sectionno=11C&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[11C. Investigation.-- (1) Where the Board has reasonable ground to believe that---`
  line
  line `(a) the transactions in securities are being dealt with in a manner detrimental to the investors or`
  line `the securities market; or`
  line
  line `(b) any intermediary or any person associated with the securities market has violated any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules or the regulations made or directions issued by the Board`
  line thereunder,
  line
  line `it may, at any time by order in writing, direct any person (hereafter in this section referred to as the`
  line `Investigating Authority) specified in the order to investigate the affairs of such intermediary or persons`
  line `associated with the securities market and to report thereon to the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sections 235 to 241 of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956), it shall be the duty of every manager, managing director, officer and other employee of the`
  line `company and every intermediary referred to in section 12 or every person associated with the securities`
  line `market to preserve and to produce to the Investigating Authority or any person authorised by it in this`
  line `behalf, all the books, registers, other documents and record of, or relating to, the company or, as the case`
  line `may be, of or relating to, the intermediary or such person, which are in their custody or power.`
  line
  line `(3) The Investigating Authority may require any intermediary or any person associated with securities`
  line `market in any manner to furnish such information to, or produce such books, or registers, or other`
  line `documents, or record before it or any person authorised by it in this behalf as it may consider necessary if`
  line `the furnishing of such information or the production of such books, or registers, or other documents, or`
  line `record is relevant or necessary for the purposes of its investigation.`
  line
  line `(4) The Investigating Authority may keep in its custody any books, registers, other documents and`
  line `record produced under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) for six months and thereafter shall return the`
  line `same to any intermediary or any person associated with securities market by whom or on whose behalf`
  line `the books, registers, other documents and record are produced:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Investigating Authority may call for any book, register, other document and record`
  line `if they are needed again:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the person on whose behalf the books, registers, other documents and record`
  line `are produced requires certified copies of the books, registers, other documents and record produced before`
  line `the Investigating Authority, it shall give certified copies of such books, registers, other documents and`
  line `record to such person or on whose behalf the books, registers, other documents and record were produced.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person, directed to make an investigation under sub-section (1), may examine on oath, any`
  line `manager, managing director, officer and other employee of any intermediary or any person associated`
  line `with securities market in any manner, in relation to the affairs of his business and may administer an oath`
  line `accordingly and for that purpose may require any of those persons to appear before it personally.`
  line
  line `(6) If any person fails without reasonable cause or refuses--`
  line
  line `(a) to produce to the Investigating Authority or any person authorised by it in this behalf any`
  line `book, register, other document and record which is his duty under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) to`
  line `produce; or`
  line
  line `(b) to furnish any information which is his duty under sub-section (3) to furnish; or`
  line
  line `(c) to appear before the Investigating Authority personally when required to do so under`
  line `sub-section (5) or to answer any question which is put to him by the Investigating Authority in`
  line `pursuance of that sub-section; or`
  line
  line `(d) to sign the notes of any examination referred to in sub-section (7),`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, which`
  line `may extend to one crore rupees, or with both, and also with a further fine which may extend to five lakh`
  line `rupees for every day after the first during which the failure or refusal continues.`
  line
  line `(7) Notes of any examination under sub-section (5) shall be taken down in writing and shall be read`
  line `over to, or by, and signed by, the person examined, and may thereafter be used in evidence against him.`
  line
  line `(8) Where in the course of investigation, the Investigating Authority has reasonable ground to believe`
  line `that the books, registers, other documents and record of, or relating to, any intermediary or any person`
  line `associated with securities market in any manner, may be destroyed, mutilated, altered, falsified or`
  line `secreted, the Investigating Authority may make an application to ^3[the Magistrate or Judge of such`
  line `designated court in Mumbai, as may be notified by the Central Government] for an order for the seizure`
  line `of such books, registers, other documents and record.`
  line
  line `^4[(8A) The authorised officer may requisition the services of any police officer or any officer of the`
  line `Central Government, or of both, to assist him for all or any of the purposes specified in sub-section (8)`
  line `and it shall be the duty of every such officer to comply with such requisition.]`
  line
  line `(9) After considering the application and hearing the Investigating Authority, if necessary, ^5[the Magistrate or Judge of the Designated Court] may, by order, authorise the Investigating Authority---`
  line
  line `(a) to enter, with such assistance, as may be required, the place or places where such books,`
  line `registers, other documents and record are kept;`
  line
  line `(b) to search that place or those places in the manner specified in the order; and`
  line
  line `(c) to seize books, registers, other documents and record, it considers necessary for the purposes`
  line `of the investigation:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^5[the Magistrate or Judge of the Designated Court] shall not authorise seizure of`
  line `books, registers, other documents and record, of any listed public company or a public company (not`
  line `being the intermediaries specified under section 12) which intends to get its securities listed on any`
  line `recognised stock exchange unless such company indulges in insider trading or market manipulation.`
  line
  line `(10) The Investigating Authority shall keep in its custody the books, registers, other documents and`
  line `record seized under this section for such period not later than the conclusion of the investigation as it`
  line `considers necessary and thereafter shall return the same to the company or the other body corporate, or, as`
  line `the case may be, to the managing director or the manager or any other person, from whose custody or`
  line `power they were seized and inform ^4[the Magistrate or Judge of the Designated Court] of such return:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Investigating Authority may, before returning such books, registers, other`
  line `documents and record as aforesaid, place identification marks on them or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(11) Save as otherwise provided in this section, every search or seizure made under this section shall`
  line `be carried out in accordance with the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)`
  line `relating to searches or seizures made under that Code.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 6 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995)`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 6 (w.e.f. 29-10-2002)`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 5, for "the Judicial Magistrate of the first class having jurisdiction" (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-3-2014).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "the Magistrate" (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_d:
  sectionId (4667)
  sectionNo 11D
  orderNo 17
  title `Cease and desist proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 6 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4667&sectionno=11D&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_11_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[11D. Cease and desist proceedings.-- If the Board finds, after causing an inquiry to be made, that`
  line `any person has violated, or is likely to violate, any provisions of this Act, or any rules or regulations made`
  line `thereunder, it may pass an order requiring such person to cease and desist from committing or causing`
  line `such violation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall not pass such order in respect of any listed public company or a public`
  line `company (other than the intermediaries specified under section 12) which intends to get its securities`
  line `listed on any recognised stock exchange unless the Board has reasonable grounds to believe that such`
  line `company has indulged in insider trading or market manipulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (4668)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 18
  title `Registration of stock-brokers, sub-brokers, share transfer agents, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4668&sectionno=12&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) No stock-broker,`
  line `sub-broker, share transfer agent, banker to an issue, trustee of trust deed, registrar to an issue, merchant`
  line `banker, underwriter, portfolio manager, investment adviser and such other intermediary who may be`
  line `associated with securities market shall buy, sell or deal in securities except under, and in accordance with,`
  line `the conditions of a certificate of registration obtained from the Board in accordance with the`
  line `^1[regulations] made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person buying or selling securities or otherwise dealing with the securities market as a`
  line `stock-broker, sub-broker, share transfer agent, banker to an issue, trustee of trust deed, registrar to an`
  line `issue, merchant banker, underwriter, portfolio manager, investment adviser and such other intermediary`
  line `who may be associated with securities market immediately before the establishment of the Board for`
  line `which no registration certificate was necessary prior to such establishment, may continue to do so for a`
  line `period of three months from such establishment or, if he has made an application for such registration`
  line `within the said period of three months, till the disposal of such application:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that any certificate of registration, obtained immediately before the commencement`
  line `of the Securities Laws (Amendment) Act, 1995 (9 of 1995), shall be deemed to have been obtained from`
  line `the Board in accordance with the regulations providing for such registration.]`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) No ^3[depository, participant, custodian] of securities, foreign institutional investor, credit rating`
  line `agency or any other intermediary associated with the securities market as the Board may by notification in`
  line `this behalf specify, shall buy or sell or deal in securities except under and in accordance with the`
  line `conditions of a certificate of registration obtained from the Board in accordance with the regulations made`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person buying or selling securities or otherwise dealing with the securities market as a`
  line `^3[depository, participant, custodian] of securities, foreign institutional investor or credit rating agency`
  line `immediately before the commencement of the Securities Laws (Amendment) Act, 1995 (9 of 1995), for`
  line `which no certificate of registration was required prior to such commencement, may continue to buy or sell`
  line `securities or otherwise deal with the securities market until such time regulations are made under clause`
  line `(d) of sub-section (2) of section 30.`
  line
  line `(1B) No person shall sponsor or cause to be sponsored or carry on or cause to be carried on any`
  line `venture capital funds or collective investment scheme including mutual funds, unless he obtains a`
  line `certificate of registration from the Board in accordance with the regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person sponsoring or causing to be sponsored, carrying or causing to be carried on`
  line `any venture capital funds or collective investment scheme operating in the securities market immediately`
  line `before the commencement of the Securities Laws (Amendment) Act, 1995 (9 of 1995) for which no`
  line `certificate of registration was required prior to such commencement, may continue to operate till such`
  line `time regulations are made under clause (d) of sub-section (2) of section 30.]`
  line
  line `^4[(IC) No person shall sponsor or cause to be sponsored or carry on or cause to be carried on the`
  line `activity of an alternative investment fund or a business trust as defined in clause (13A) of section 2 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), unless a certificate or registration is granted by the Board in`
  line `accordance with the regulations made under this Act.]`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that, for the purposes of this section,`
  line `a collective investment scheme or mutual fund shall not include any unit linked insurance policy or scrips`
  line `or any such instrument or unit, by whatever name called, which provides a component of investment`
  line `besides the component of insurance issued by an insurer.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for registration shall be in such manner and on payment of such fees as may be`
  line `determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may, by order, suspend or cancel a certificate of registration in such manner as may be`
  line `determined by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order under this sub-section shall be made unless the person concerned has been`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 7, for rules (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 22 of 1996, s. 30 and the Schedule, for depository, custodian (w.e.f. 20-9-1995).`
  line
  line `4.Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 159 (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 26 of 2010, s. 4 (w.e.f. 9-4-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (4669)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 19
  title `Prohibition of manipulative and deceptive devices, insider trading and substantial acquisition of securities or control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 7 (w.e.f. 29-10-2002). br`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4669&sectionno=12A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Prohibition of manipulative and deceptive devices, insider trading and substantial`
  line `acquisition of securities or control.-- No person shall directly or indirectly--`
  line
  line `(a) use or employ, in connection with the issue, purchase or sale of any securities listed or`
  line `proposed to be listed on a recognised stock exchange, any manipulative or deceptive device or`
  line `contrivance in contravention of the provisions of this Act or the rules or the regulations made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(b) employ any device, scheme or artifice to defraud in connection with issue or dealing in`
  line `securities which are listed or proposed to be listed on a recognised stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(c) engage in any act, practice, course of business which operates or would operate as fraud or`
  line `deceit upon any person, in connection with the issue, dealing in securities which are listed or`
  line `proposed to be listed on a recognised stock exchange, in contravention of the provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules or the regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(d) engage in insider trading;`
  line
  line `(e) deal in securities while in possession of material or non-public information or communicate`
  line `such material or non-public information to any other person, in a manner which is in contravention of`
  line `the provisions of this Act or the rules or the regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(f) acquire control of any company or securities more than the percentage of equity share capital`
  line `of a company whose securities are listed or proposed to be listed on a recognised stock exchange in`
  line `contravention of the regulations made under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (4670)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 20
  title `Grants by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4670&sectionno=13&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Board grants of such sums of money as that`
  line `Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (4671)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 21
  title Fund.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4671&sectionno=14&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a Fund to be called the Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India General Fund and there shall be credited thereto---`
  line
  line `(a) all grants, fees and charges received by the Board under this Act; ^1***`
  line
  line ^2*****
  line
  line `(b) all sums received by the Board from such other sources as may be decided upon by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Fund shall be applied for meeting--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the members, officers and other employees`
  line `of the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the expenses of the Board in the discharge of its functions under section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) the expenses on objects and for purposes authorised by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and" omitted by Act 9 of 1995, s. 8 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `2. Clause (aa) omitted by Act 59 of 2002, s. 8 (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (4672)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 22
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4672&sectionno=15&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any other person appointed by him in`
  line `connection with the audit of the accounts of the Board shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (4673)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 23
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish information, return, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4673&sectionno=15A&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Penalty for failure to furnish information, return, etc-- If any person, who is required under`
  line `this Act or any rules or regulations made thereunder,---`
  line
  line `(a) to furnish any document, return or report to the Board, fails to furnish the same, ^2[or who`
  line `furnishes or files false, incorrect or incomplete information, return, report, books or other documents] he shall be liable to ^3[a penalty ^4[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees for each day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees;]]`
  line
  line `(b) to file any return or furnish any information, books or other documents within the time`
  line `specified therefor in the regulations, fails to file return or furnish the same within the time specified`
  line `therefor in the regulations, he shall be liable to ^5[a penalty ^3[which shall not be less than one lakh`
  line `rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues`
  line `subject to a maximum of one crore rupees;]]`
  line
  line `(c) to maintain books of account or records, fails to maintain the same, he shall be liable to ^6[a penalty ^3[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for`
  line `each day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 181 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 9, for "a penalty not exceeding one lakh and fifty thousand rupees for each such failure" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 9, for "a penalty not exceeding five thousand rupees for every day during which such failure continues" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "a penalty not exceeding ten thousand rupees for every day during which such failure continues" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (4674)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 24
  title `Penalty for failure by any person to enter into agreement with clients.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4674&sectionno=15B&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[15B. Penalty for failure by any person to enter into agreement with clients.-- If any person, who`
  line `is registered as an intermediary and is required under this Act or any rules or regulations made thereunder`
  line `to enter into an agreement with his client, fails to enter into such agreement, he shall be liable to ^2[a penalty ^3[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each`
  line `day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995)/b`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "a penalty not exceeding five lakh rupees for every such failure" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 7, for certain words (w.e.f.8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_c:
  sectionId (4675)
  sectionNo 15C
  orderNo 25
  title `Penalty for failure to redress investors‟ grievances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4675&sectionno=15C&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[15C. Penalty for failure to redress investors’ grievances.—If any listed company or any person`
  line `who is registered as an intermediary, after having been called upon by the Board in writing ^2[including by`
  line `by any means of electronic communication], to redress the grievances of investors, fails to redress such`
  line `grievances within the time specified by the Board, such company or intermediary shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty ^3[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each`
  line `day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees].]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 11, for section 15C (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 183 (w.e.f. 20-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 8, for certain words (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_d:
  sectionId (4676)
  sectionNo 15D
  orderNo 26
  title `Penalty for certain defaults in case of mutual funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4676&sectionno=15D&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[15D. Penalty for certain defaults in case of mutual funds---- If any person, who is---`
  line
  line `(a) required under this Act or any rules or regulations made thereunder to obtain a certificate of`
  line `registration from the Board for sponsoring or carrying on any collective investment scheme, including`
  line `mutual funds, sponsors or carries on any collective investment scheme, including mutual funds,`
  line `without obtaining such certificate of registration, he shall be liable to ^2[a penalty^3[which shall not`
  line `be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each day during which he`
  line `sponsors or carries on any such collective investment scheme including mutual funds subject to a`
  line `maximum of one crore rupees;]]`
  line
  line `(b) registered with the Board as a collective investment scheme, including mutual funds, for`
  line `sponsoring or carrying on any investment scheme, fails to comply with the terms and conditions of`
  line `certificate of registration, he shall be liable to ^4[a penalty ^5[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues`
  line `subject to a maximum of one crore rupees;]]`
  line
  line `(c) registered with the Board as a collective investment scheme including mutual funds, fails to`
  line `make an application for listing of its schemes as provided for in the regulations governing such`
  line `listing, he shall be liable to ^6[a penalty ^4[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may`
  line `extend to one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of`
  line `one crore rupees;]]`
  line
  line `(d) registered as a collective investment scheme, including mutual funds, fails to despatch unit`
  line `certificates of any scheme in the manner provided in the regulation governing such despatch, he shall be liable to ^6[a penalty ^4[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one`
  line `lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore`
  line rupees;]]
  line
  line `(e) registered as collective investment scheme, including mutual funds, fails to refund the`
  line `application monies paid by the investors within the period specified in the regulations, he shall be`
  line `liable to ^8[a penalty ^4[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees for each day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees;]]`
  line
  line `(f) registered as a collective investment scheme, including mutual funds, fails to invest money`
  line `collected by such collective investment schemes in the manner or within the period specified in the`
  line `regulations, he shall be liable to ^9[a penalty ^4[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which`
  line `may extend to one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues subject to a`
  line `maximum of one crore rupees.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995). br`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 12, for "a penalty not exceeding ten thousand rupees for each day during which he carries on any such collective`
  line `investment scheme including mutual funds, or ten lakh rupees, whichever is higher" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 12, for "a penalty not exceeding ten thousand rupees for each day during which such failure`
  line `continues or ten lakh rupees, whichever is higher" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f.8-9-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "a penalty not exceeding five thousand rupees for each day during which such failure continues"`
  line `(w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f.8-9-2014).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 12, for a penalty not exceeding five thousand rupees for each day during which such failure`
  line `Continues (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for a penalty not exceeding one thousand rupees for each day during which such failure continue`
  line `(w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_e:
  sectionId (4677)
  sectionNo 15E
  orderNo 27
  title `Penalty for failure to observe rules and regulations by an asset management company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4677&sectionno=15E&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[15E. Penalty for failure to observe rules and regulations by an asset management company.-- Where any asset management company of a mutual fund registered under this Act fails to comply with`
  line `any of the regulations providing for restrictions on the activities of the asset management companies, such`
  line `asset management company shall be liable to ^2[a penalty ^3[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees`
  line `but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues subject to a`
  line `maximum of one crore rupees.]]]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995). br`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "a penalty not exceeding five lakh rupees for each such failure" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 10, for certain words (w.e.f.8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_ea:
  sectionId (48990)
  sectionNo 15EA
  orderNo 28
  title `Penalty for default in case of alternative investment funds, infrastructure investment trusts and real estate investment trusts.`
  content `^1[15EA. Penalty for default in case of alternative investment funds, infrastructure investment trusts and real estate investment trusts.-- Where any person fails to comply with the regulations made by the Board in respect of alternative investment funds, infrastructure investment trusts and real estate investment trusts or fails to comply with the directions issued by the Board, such person shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees or three times the amount of gains made out of such failure, whichever is higher.]`
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 182 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=48990&sectionno=15EA&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_eb:
  sectionId (48991)
  sectionNo 15EB
  orderNo 29
  title `Penalty for default in case of investment adviser and research analyst.`
  content `^1[^2[15EB. Penalty for default in case of investment adviser and research analyst.--Where an investment adviser or a research analyst fails to comply with the regulations made by the Board or directions issued by the Board, such investment adviser or research analyst shall be liable to penalty which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees.]]`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_eb_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=48991&sectionno=15EB&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_eb_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995). br`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 182 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_f:
  sectionId (4678)
  sectionNo 15F
  orderNo 30
  title `Penalty for default in case of stock brokers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_f_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_f_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4678&sectionno=15F&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[15F. Penalty for default in case of stock brokers---- If any person, who is registered as a stock`
  line `broker under this Act,---`
  line
  line `(a) fails to issue contract notes in the form and manner specified by the stock exchange of which`
  line `such broker is a member, he shall be liable to ^2[a penalty which shall not be less than one lakh rupees`
  line `but which may extend to ^3[one crore rupees]] for which the contract note was required to be issued by that broker;`
  line
  line `(b) fails to deliver any security or fails to make payment of the amount due to the investor in the`
  line `manner within the period specified in the regulations, he shall be liable to ^4[a penalty`
  line
  line `^5[which shall`
  line `not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each day during which^6[such failure continues] subject to a maximum of one crore rupees]];`
  line
  line `(c) charges an amount of brokerage which is in excess of the brokerage specified in the`
  line `regulations, he shall be liable to ^7[a penalty ^8[[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which`
  line `may extend to five times the amount of brokerage]] charged in excess of the specified brokerage,`
  line `whichever is higher.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_f_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995). br`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 11, for "a penalty not exceeding five times the amount" (w.e.f.8-9-2014).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 184 (w.e.f. 20-1-2020).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 14, for "a penalty not exceeding five thousand rupees for each day during which such failure`
  line `continues" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 11, for certain words (w.e.f.8-9-2014).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 183, for "he sponsors or carries on any such collective investment scheme including mutual fund"`
  line `(w.e.f. 8-3-2019)..`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 14, for "a penalty not exceeding five thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 11, for "of one lakh rupees or five times the amount of brokerage" (w.e.f.8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_g:
  sectionId (4679)
  sectionNo 15G
  orderNo 31
  title `Penalty for insider trading.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_g_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_g_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4679&sectionno=15G&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[15G. Penalty for insider trading.-- If any insider who,`
  line
  line `(i) either on his own behalf or on behalf of any other person, deals in securities of a body`
  line `corporate listed on any stock exchange on the basis of any unpublished price sensitive information; or`
  line
  line `(ii) communicates any unpublished price sensitive information to any person, with or without his`
  line `request for such information except as required in the ordinary course of business or under any law;`
  line or
  line
  line `(iii) counsels, or procures for any other person to deal in any securities of any body corporate on`
  line `the basis of unpublished price sensitive information,`
  line
  line `shall be liable to a penalty ^2[which shall not be less than ten lakh rupees but which may extend to`
  line `twenty-five crore rupees or three times the amount of profits made out of insider trading, whichever is`
  line higher].]
obj_root_law_sections_15_g_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995). br`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s.12, for certain words (w.e.f.8-2-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_h:
  sectionId (4680)
  sectionNo 15H
  orderNo 32
  title `Penalty for non-disclosure of acquisition of shares and takeovers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4680&sectionno=15H&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[15H. Penalty for non-disclosure of acquisition of shares and takeovers.-- If any person, who is`
  line `required under this Act or any rules or regulations made thereunder, fails to`
  line
  line `(i) disclose the aggregate of his share holding in the body corporate before he acquires any shares`
  line `of that body corporate; or`
  line
  line `(ii) make a public announcement to acquire shares at a minimum price;`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) make a public offer by sending letter of offer to the shareholders of the concerned`
  line `company; or`
  line
  line `(iv) make payment of consideration to the shareholders who sold their shares pursuant to letter of`
  line offer],
  line
  line `he shall be liable to a penalty ^3[which shall not be less than ten lakh rupees but which may extend to`
  line `twenty-five crore rupees or three times the amount of profits made out of such failure, whichever is`
  line higher].
obj_root_law_sections_15_h_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995). br`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 16 (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s.13, for certain words (w.e.f.8-2-2014)br`
obj_root_law_sections_15_ha:
  sectionId (4681)
  sectionNo 15HA
  orderNo 33
  title `Penalty for fraudulent and unfair trade practices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_ha_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_ha_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4681&sectionno=15HA&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_ha_content:
  string
  line `^1[15HA. Penalty for fraudulent and unfair trade practices.--If any person indulges in fraudulent`
  line `and unfair trade practices relating to securities, he shall be liable to a penalty ^2[which shall not be less`
  line `than five lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five crore rupees or three times the amount of`
  line `profits made out of such practices, whichever is higher].]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_ha_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 17 (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 14, for certain words (w.e.f. 8-2-2014). br`
obj_root_law_sections_15_haa:
  sectionId (49797)
  sectionNo 15HAA
  orderNo 34
  title `Penalty for alteration, destruction, etc., of records and failure to protect the electronic database of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_haa_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 185 (w.e.f. 20-1-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=49797&sectionno=15HAA&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_haa_content:
  string
  line `^1[15HAA. Penalty for alteration, destruction, etc., of records and failure to protect the`
  line `electronic database of Board.--Any person, who--`
  line
  line `(a) knowingly alters, destroys, mutilates, conceals, falsifies, or makes a false entry in any`
  line `information, record, document (including electronic records), which is required under this Act or any`
  line `rules or regulations made there under, so as to impede, obstruct, or influence the investigation,`
  line `inquiry, audit, inspection or proper administration of any matter within the jurisdiction of the Board.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, a person shall be deemed to have altered,`
  line `concealed or destroyed such information, record or document, in case he knowingly fails to`
  line `immediately report the matter to the Board or fails to preserve the same till such information`
  line `continues to be relevant to any investigation, inquiry, audit, inspection or proceeding, which may be`
  line `initiated by the Board and conclusion thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) without being authorised to do so, access or tries to access, or denies of access or modifies`
  line `access parameters, to the regulatory data in the database;`
  line
  line `(c) without being authorised to do so, downloads, extracts, copies, or reproduces in any form the`
  line `regulatory data maintained in the system database;`
  line
  line `(d) knowingly introduces any computer virus or other computer contaminant into the system`
  line `database and brings out a trading halt;`
  line
  line `(e) without authorisation disrupts the functioning of system database;`
  line
  line `(f) knowingly damages, destroys, deletes, alters, diminishes in value or utility, or affects by any`
  line `means, the regulatory data in the system database; or`
  line
  line `(g) knowingly provides any assistance to or causes any other person to do any of the acts`
  line `specified in clauses (a) to (f), shall be liable to a penalty which shall not be less than one lakh rupees`
  line `but which may extend to ten crore rupees or three times the amount of profits made out of such act,`
  line `whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the expressions "computer contaminant", "computer virus" and`
  line `"damage" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them under section 43 of the Information`
  line `Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000).]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_hb:
  sectionId (4682)
  sectionNo 15HB
  orderNo 35
  title `Penalty for contravention where no separate penalty has been provided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_hb_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_hb_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=4682&sectionno=15HB&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_hb_content:
  string
  line `^1[15HB. Penalty for contravention where no separate penalty has been provided.-- Whoever fails`
  line `to comply with any provision of this Act, the rules or the regulations made or directions issued by the`
  line `Board thereunder for which no separate penalty has been provided, shall be ^2[liable to a penalty which`
  line `shall not be less one lakh rupees but which may extend to one crore rupees].]]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_hb_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995). br`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "liable to a penalty which may extend to one crore rupees" (w.e.f. 8-2-2014). br`
obj_root_law_sections_15_i:
  sectionId (31441)
  sectionNo 15-I
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to adjudicate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31441&sectionno=15-I&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[15-I. Power to adjudicate.-- (1) For the purpose of adjudging under sections 15A, 15B, 15C, 15D,`
  line `15E, ^2[15EA,15EB,] 15F, 15G,`
  line `^3[15H, 15HA and 15HB] the Board ^4[may] appoint any officer not below the rank of a`
  line `Division Chief to be an adjudicating officer for holding an inquiry in the prescribed manner after giving`
  line `any person concerned a reasonable opportunity of being heard for the purpose of imposing any penalty.`
  line
  line `(2) While holding an inquiry the adjudicating officer shall have power to summon and enforce the`
  line `attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to`
  line `produce any document which in the opinion of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for or relevant to`
  line `the subject matter of the inquiry and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person has failed to comply`
  line `with the provisions of any of the sections specified in sub-section (1), he may impose such penalty as he`
  line `thinks fit in accordance with the provisions of any of those sections.`
  line
  line `^5[(3) The Board may call for and examine the record of any proceedings under this section and if it`
  line `considers that the order passed by the adjudicating officer is erroneous to the extent it is not in the`
  line `interests of the securities market, it may, after making or causing to be made such inquiry as it deems`
  line `necessary, pass an order enhancing the quantum of penalty, if the circumstances of the case so justify:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be passed unless the person concerned has been given an opportunity`
  line `of being heard in the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this sub-section shall be applicable after an expiry of a`
  line `period of three months from the date of the order passed by the adjudicating officer or disposal of the`
  line `appeal under section 15T, whichever is earlier.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_i_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995). br`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 184 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 18, for "and 15H" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 184, for "shall" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 16 (w.e.f. 28-3-2014).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 16 (w.e.f. 28-3-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_j:
  sectionId (31442)
  sectionNo 15J
  orderNo 37
  title `Factors to be taken into account while adjudging quantum of penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_j_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_j_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31442&sectionno=15J&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_j_content:
  string
  line `15J. ^1[Factors to be taken into account while adjudging quantum of penalty].--While adjudging the quantum`
  line `of penalty under section ^2[15-I or section 11 or section 11B, the Board or the adjudicating officer] officer shall have due regard to the following factors,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of disproportionate gain or unfair advantage, wherever quantifiable, made as a`
  line `result of the default;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of loss caused to an investor or group of investors as a result of the default;`
  line
  line `(c) the repetitive nature of the default.`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is clarified that the power of ^4*** to`
  line `adjudge the quantum of penalty under sections 15A to 15E, clauses (b) and (c) of section 15F, 15G, 15H`
  line `and 15HA shall be and shall always be deemed to have been exercised under the provisions of this`
  line section.]]
obj_root_law_sections_15_j_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 185, for marginal heading (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).2`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 185, ibid., for section 15-I, the adjudicating officer (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).2`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s.147 (w.e.f. 1-3-2017).`
  line
  line `4. The words "of an adjudicating officer" omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 185 (w.e.f. 8-3-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_ja:
  sectionId (31443)
  sectionNo 15JA
  orderNo 38
  title `Crediting sums realised by way of penalties to Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_ja_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-10-2002)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31443&sectionno=15JA&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_ja_content:
  string
  line `^1[15JA. Crediting sums realised by way of penalties to Consolidated Fund of India.--All sums`
  line `realised by way of penalties under this Act shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India].`
obj_root_law_sections_15_jb:
  sectionId (31444)
  sectionNo 15JB
  orderNo 39
  title `Settlement of administrative and civil proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_jb_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_jb_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31444&sectionno=15JB&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_jb_content:
  string
  line `^1[15JB. Settlement of administrative and civil proceedings.--(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, any person, against whom any proceedings have`
  line `been initiated or may be initiated under section 11, section 11B, section 11D, sub-section (3) of section 12`
  line `or section 15-I, may file an application in writing to the Board proposing for settlement of the proceedings`
  line `initiated or to be initiated for the alleged defaults.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, after taking into consideration the nature, gravity and impact of defaults, agree to`
  line `the proposal for settlement, on payment of such sum by the defaulter or on such other terms as may be`
  line `determined by the Board in accordance with the regulations made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The settlement proceedings under this section shall be conducted in accordance with the`
  line `procedure specified in the regulations made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) No appeal shall lie under section 15T against any order passed by the Board or adjudicating`
  line `officer, as the case may be, under this section.`
  line
  line `^2[(5) All settlement amounts, excluding the disgorgement amount and legal costs, realised under this`
  line `Act shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_jb_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 17 (w.e.f. 20-4-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 186 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_k:
  sectionId (31445)
  sectionNo 15K
  orderNo 40
  title `Establishment of Securities Appellate Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_k_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 148, ibid., for section 15K (w.e.f. 1-3-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31445&sectionno=15K&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[15K. Establishment of Securities Appellate Tribunal.--(1) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification, establish a Tribunal to be known as the Securities Appellate Tribunal to exercise the`
  line `jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on it by or under this Act or any other law for the time being`
  line `in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall also specify in the notification referred to in sub-section (1), the`
  line `matters and places in relation to which the Securities Appellate Tribunal may exercise jurisdiction.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_l:
  sectionId (31446)
  sectionNo 15L
  orderNo 41
  title `Composition of Securities Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_l_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s.148, ibid., for section 15L (w.e.f.1-3-2017)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31446&sectionno=15L&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[15L. Composition of Securities Appellate.--(1) The Securities Appellate Tribunal shall consist of`
  line `a Presiding Officer and such number of Judicial Members and Technical Members as the Central`
  line `Government may determine, by notification, to exercise the powers and discharge the functions conferred`
  line `on the Securities Appellate Tribunal under this Act or any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the Securities Appellate Tribunal may be exercised by Benches thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) a Bench may be constituted by the Presiding Officer of the Securities Appellate Tribunal with`
  line `two or more Judicial or Technical Members as he may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that every Bench constituted shall include at least one Judicial Member and one Technical`
  line Member;
  line
  line `(c) the Benches of the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall ordinarily sit at Mumbai and may also sit`
  line `at such other places as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Presiding Officer, notify.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Presiding Officer may transfer a`
  line `Judicial Member or a Technical Member of the Securities Appellate Tribunal from one Bench to another`
  line Bench.]
obj_root_law_sections_15_m:
  sectionId (31447)
  sectionNo 15M
  orderNo 42
  title `Qualification for appointment as Presiding Officer or Member of Securities Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_m_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 148, ibid., for section 15M (w.e.f. 1-3-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31447&sectionno=15M&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_m_content:
  string
  line `^1[15M. Qualification for appointment as Presiding Officer, Judicial Member and Technical`
  line `Member.-- A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the Presiding Officer or a Judicial Member`
  line `or a Technical Member of the Securities Appellate Tribunal, unless he`
  line
  line `(a) is, or has been, a Judge of the Supreme Court or a Chief Justice of a High Court or a Judge of`
  line `High Court for at least seven years, in the case of the Presiding Officer; and`
  line
  line `(b) is, or has been, a Judge of High Court for at least five years, in the case of a Judicial Member;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a Technical Member`
  line
  line `(i) is, or has been, a Secretary or an Additional Secretary in the Ministry or Department of the`
  line `Central Government or any equivalent post in the Central Government or a State Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is a person of proven ability, integrity and standing having special knowledge and`
  line `professional experience, of not less than fifteen years, in financial sector including securities`
  line `market or pension funds or commodity derivatives or insurance.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_ma:
  sectionId (44386)
  sectionNo 15MA
  orderNo 43
  title `Amendment of Presiding Officer and Judicial Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_ma_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=44386&sectionno=15MA&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_ma_content:
  string
  line `^1[15MA. Appointment of Presiding Officer and Judicial Member.-- The Presiding Officer and`
  line `Judicial Members of the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be appointed by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the Chief Justice of India or his nominee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_mb:
  sectionId (44387)
  sectionNo 15MB
  orderNo 44
  title `Search-cum-Selection Committee for appointment of Technical Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_mb_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=44387&sectionno=15MB&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_mb_content:
  string
  line `^1[15MB. Search-cum-Selection Committee for appointment of Technical Members.-- (1) The`
  line `Technical Members of the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be appointed by the Central Government on`
  line `the recommendation of a Search-cum-Selection Committee consisting of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Presiding Officer, Securities Appellate Tribunal-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary, Department of Economic Affairs-Member;`
  line
  line `(c) Secretary, Department of Financial Services-Member; and`
  line
  line `(d) Secretary, Legislative Department or Secretary, Department of Legal Affairs-Member.`
  line
  line `(2) The Secretary, Department of Economic Affairs shall be the Convener of the Search-cumSelection Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) The Search-cum-Selection Committee shall determine its procedure for recommending the names`
  line `of persons to be appointed under sub-section (1).]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_mc:
  sectionId (44388)
  sectionNo 15MC
  orderNo 45
  title `Vacancy not to invalidate selection proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_mc_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=44388&sectionno=15MC&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_mc_content:
  string
  line `^1[15MC. Vacancy not to invalidate selection proceeding.-- (1) No appointment of the Presiding`
  line `Officer, a Judicial Member or a Technical Member of the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be invalid`
  line `merely by reason of any vacancy or any defect in the constitution of the Search-cum-Selection`
  line Committee.
  line
  line `(2) A member or part time member of the Board or the Insurance Regulatory and Development`
  line `Authority or the Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority, or any person at senior`
  line `management level equivalent to the Executive Director in the Board or in such Authorities, shall not be`
  line `appointed as Presiding Officer or Member of the Securities Appellate Tribunal, during his service or`
  line `tenure as such with the Board or with such Authorities, as the case may be, or within two years from the`
  line `date on which he ceases to hold office as such in the Board or in such Authorities.`
  line
  line `(3) The Presiding Officer or such other member of the Securities Appellate Tribunal, holding office`
  line `on the date of commencement of Part VIII of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017) shall`
  line `continue to hold office for such term as he was appointed and the other provisions of this Act shall apply`
  line `to such Presiding Officer or such other member, as if Part VIII of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017`
  line `had not been enacted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_n:
  sectionId (31448)
  sectionNo 15N
  orderNo 46
  title `Tenure of office of Presiding Officer and other Members of Securities Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_n_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s.148, for section 15N (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31448&sectionno=15N&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[15N. Tenure of office of Presiding Office, Judicial or Technical Members of Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal.--The Presiding Officer or every Judicial or Technical Member of the Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal shall hold office for a term of five years from the date on which he enters upon his`
  line `office, and shall be eligible for reappointment for another term of maximum five years:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Presiding Officer or the Judicial or Technical Member shall hold office after he has`
  line `attained the age of seventy years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_o:
  sectionId (31449)
  sectionNo 15O
  orderNo 47
  title `Salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Presiding Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_o_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_o_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31449&sectionno=15O&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[15-O. Salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of Presiding Officers.-- The salary and allowances payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service (including pension,`
  line `gratuity and other retirement benefits) of, the ^2[Presiding Officer and other Members of a Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal] shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of services of the`
  line `^3[Presiding Officer and other Members of a Securities Appellate Tribunal] shall be varied to their`
  line `disadvantage after appointment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_o_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 22, for "Presiding Officer of a Securities Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for "said Presiding Officers" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_p:
  sectionId (31450)
  sectionNo 15P
  orderNo 48
  title `Filling up of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_p_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_p_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31450&sectionno=15P&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[15P. Filling up of vacancies.-- If, for reason other than temporary absence, any vacancy occurs in`
  line `^2t[he office of the Presiding Officer or any other Member], of a Securities Appellate Tribunal, then the`
  line `Central Government shall appoint another person in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill the`
  line `vacancy and the proceedings may be continued before the Securities Appellate Tribunal from the stage at`
  line `which the vacancy is filled.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_p_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for "office of the Presiding Officer" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_pa:
  sectionId (48994)
  sectionNo 15PA
  orderNo 49
  title `Member to act as Presiding Officer in certain circumstances`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_pa_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 148 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=48994&sectionno=15PA&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_pa_content:
  string
  line `^1[15PA. Member to act as Presiding Officer in certain circumstances.--In the event of occurrence`
  line `of any vacancy in the office of the Presiding Officer of the Securities Appellate Tribunal by reason of his`
  line `death, resignation or otherwise, the senior-most Judicial Member of the Securities Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall act as the Presiding Officer until the date on which a new Presiding Officer is appointed in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_q:
  sectionId (31451)
  sectionNo 15Q
  orderNo 50
  title `Resignation and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_q_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_q_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31451&sectionno=15Q&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_q_content:
  string
  line `^1[15Q. Resignation and removal.-- ^2(1) [The Presiding Officer or any other Member of a Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government, resign`
  line `his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that ^3[the Presiding Officer or any other Member] shall, unless he is permitted by the`
  line `Central Government to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three`
  line `months from the date of receipt of such notice or until a person duly appointed as his successor inters`
  line `upon his office or until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is the earliest.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) The Central Government may, after an inquiry made by the Judge of the Supreme Court, remove`
  line `the Presiding Officer or Judicial Member or Technical Member of the Securities Appellate Tribunal, if`
  line he--
  line
  line `(a) is, or at any time has been adjudged as an insolvent;`
  line
  line `(b) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as the Presiding Officer, Judicial or`
  line `Technical Member;`
  line
  line `(c) has been convicted of any offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude;`
  line
  line `(d) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, so abused his position as to render his`
  line `continuation in office detrimental to the public interest; or`
  line
  line `(e) has acquired such financial interest or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his`
  line `functions as the Presiding Officer or Judicial or Technical Member:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not be removed from office under clauses (d) and (e), unless he has been given`
  line `a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by rules, regulate the procedure for the investigation of`
  line `misbehaviour or incapacity of the ^5[the Presiding Officer or any other Member.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_q_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 24, for "Presiding Officer of a Securities Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for "the said Presiding Officer" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s.148, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 26-5-2017)`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 24, for "aforesaid Presiding Officer" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_qa:
  sectionId (44438)
  sectionNo 15QA
  orderNo 51
  title `Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Presiding Officer and Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_qa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_qa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=44438&sectionno=15QA&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_qa_content:
  string
  line `^1[15QA.Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Presiding Officer and`
  line `Member.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of`
  line `office, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Presiding Officer and other Members of the Appellate Tribunal appointed after the commencement of`
  line `^2[the Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Presiding Officer and Member appointed before the commencement of Part XIV of`
  line `Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall continue to be governed by the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 had not come into`
  line force.]
obj_root_law_sections_15_qa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s.178 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 17, for “Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall be governed by the provisions of section 184 of that Act” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_r:
  sectionId (31452)
  sectionNo 15R
  orderNo 52
  title `Orders constituting Appellate Tribunal to be final and not to invalidate its proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_r_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_r_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31452&sectionno=15R&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_r_content:
  string
  line `^1[15R. Orders constituting Appellate Tribunal to be final and not to invalidate its proceedings.-- No order of the Central Government appointing any person as the ^2[Presiding Officer or a Member] of a`
  line `Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be called in question in any manner, and no act or proceeding before a`
  line `Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be called in question in any manner on the ground merely of any`
  line `defect in the constitution of a Securities Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_r_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 25, for "Presiding Officer" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_s:
  sectionId (31453)
  sectionNo 15S
  orderNo 53
  title `Staff of the Securities Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_s_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31453&sectionno=15S&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_s_content:
  string
  line `^1[15S. Staff of the Securities Appellate Tribunal.-- (1) The Central Government shall provide the`
  line `Securities Appellate Tribunal with such officers and employees as that Government may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers and employees of the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall discharge their functions`
  line `under general superintendence of the Presiding Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of the officers and employees of the`
  line `Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_t:
  sectionId (31454)
  sectionNo 15T
  orderNo 54
  title `Appeal to the Securities Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_t_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_t_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31454&sectionno=15T&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_t_content:
  string
  line `^1[15T. Appeal to the Securities Appellate Tribunal.-- ^2[(1) Save as provided in sub-section (2),`
  line `any person aggrieved,--`
  line
  line `(a) by an order of the Board made, on and after the commencement of the Securities Laws`
  line `(Second Amendment) Act, 1999 (32 of 1999), under this Act, or the rules or regulations`
  line `made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) by an order made by an adjudicating officer ^3[[under this Act; or]`
  line
  line ^4[
  line `(c) by an order of the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority or the Pension Fund`
  line `Regulatory and Development Authority],`
  line
  line `may prefer an appeal to a Securities Appellate Tribunal having jurisdiction in the matter.`
  line
  line ^5****
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of forty-five days from the date`
  line `on which ^6[a copy of the order made by the Board or the adjudicating officer ^7[`
  line `or the Insurance`
  line `Regulatory and Development Authority or the Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority] as`
  line `the case may be,] is received by him and it shall be in such form and be accompanied by such fee as may`
  line `be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Securities Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said`
  line `period of forty-five days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Securities Appellate Tribunal may, after giving`
  line `the parties to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit,`
  line `confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(5) The Securities Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the ^7[Board, ^8[or`
  line `^9[or the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority or the Pension Fund Regulatory and`
  line `Development Authority, as the case may be] the parties to the appeal and to the concerned adjudicating`
  line officer.
  line
  line `(6) The appeal filed before the Securities Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with`
  line `by it as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal finally within`
  line `six months from the date of receipt of the appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_t_footnotes:
  string
