obj_root_law_sections_15_u:
  sectionId (31455)
  sectionNo 15U
  orderNo 55
  title `Procedure and powers of the Securities Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_u_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_u_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31455&sectionno=15U&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_u_content:
  string
  line `^1[15U. Procedure and powers of the Securities Appellate Tribunal.-- (1) The Securities Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall not be bound by the procedure laid down by the code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908),`
  line `but shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and, subject to the other provisions of this Act and`
  line `of any rules, the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall have powers to regulate their own procedure`
  line `including the places at which they shall have their sittings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Securities Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging their functions under`
  line `this Act, the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing an application for default or deciding it ex-parte;`
  line
  line `(g) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it`
  line ex-parte;
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every proceeding before the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial`
  line `proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196, of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court for all`
  line `the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `^2[(4) Where Benches are constituted, the Presiding Officer of the Securities Appellate Tribunal may,`
  line `from time to time make provisions as to the distribution of the business of the Securities Appellate`
  line `Tribunal amongst the Benches and also provide for the matters which may be dealt with, by each Bench.`
  line
  line `(5) On the application of any of the parties and after notice to the parties, and after hearing such of`
  line `them as he may desire to be heard, or on his own motion without such notice, the Presiding Officer of the`
  line `Securities Appellate Tribunal may transfer any case pending before one Bench, for disposal, to any other`
  line Bench.
  line
  line `(6) If a Bench of the Securities Appellate Tribunal consisting of two members differ in opinion on`
  line `any point, they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a reference to the Presiding`
  line `Officer of the Securities Appellate Tribunal who shall either hear the point or points himself or refer the`
  line `case for hearing only on such point or points by one or more of the other members of the Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal and such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of`
  line `the members of the Securities Appellate Tribunal who have heard the case, including those who first`
  line `heard it.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_u_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s.148 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_v:
  sectionId (31456)
  sectionNo 15V
  orderNo 56
  title `Right to legal representation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_v_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1999, s. 10, for section 15V (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31456&sectionno=15V&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_v_content:
  string
  line `^1[15V. Right to legal representation.--The appellant may either appear in person or authorise one`
  line `or more chartered accountants or company secretaries or cost accountants or legal practitioners or`
  line `any of its officers to present his or its case before the Securities Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "chartered accountant" means a chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) and who has obtained a certificate of`
  line `practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "company secretary" means a company secretary as defined in clause (c) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 2 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980) and who has obtained a certificate of`
  line `practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "cost accountant" means a cost accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959) and who has obtained a certificate`
  line `of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "legal practitioner" means an advocate, vakil or an attorney of any High Court, and includes a`
  line `pleader in practice.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_w:
  sectionId (31457)
  sectionNo 15W
  orderNo 57
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_w_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31457&sectionno=15W&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_w_content:
  string
  line `^1[15W. Limitation. --The provisions of the Limited Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply to an appeal made to a Securities Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_x:
  sectionId (31458)
  sectionNo 15X
  orderNo 58
  title `Presiding Officer, Members and staff of Securities Appellate Tribunals to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_x_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 26, for section 15X (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31458&sectionno=15X&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_x_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[15X. Presiding Officer, Members and staff of Securities Appellate tribunal to be public`
  line `servants.--The Presiding Officer, Members and other officers and employees of a Securities Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860)].`
obj_root_law_sections_15_y:
  sectionId (31459)
  sectionNo 15Y
  orderNo 59
  title `Civil Court not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_y_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 9 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31459&sectionno=15Y&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_y_content:
  string
  line `^1[15Y. Civil Court not to have jurisdiction.-- No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any`
  line `suit or proceeding in respect of any matter which an adjudication officer appointed under this Act or a`
  line `Securities Appellate Tribunal constituted under this Act is empowered by or under this Act to determine`
  line `and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be`
  line `taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_z:
  sectionId (31460)
  sectionNo 15Z
  orderNo 60
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_z_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 27, for section 15Z (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31460&sectionno=15Z&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_15_z_content:
  string
  line `^1[15Z. Appeal to Supreme Court.--Any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal may file an appeal to the Supreme Court within sixty days from the date of`
  line `communication of the decision or order of the Securities Appellate Tribunal to him on any question of`
  line `law arising out of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not`
  line `exceeding sixty days.]]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (31461)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 61
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1996, s. 30 and the Schedule, for this Act (w.e.f. 20-9-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31461&sectionno=16&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Board shall, in exercise of its powers or the performance of its functions under`
  line ^1
  line `[this Act or the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996)], be bound by such directions on questions of policy`
  line `as the Central Government may give in writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Board shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (31462)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31462&sectionno=17&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any time the Central`
  line `Government is of opinion--`
  line
  line `(a) that on account of grave emergency, the Board is unable to discharge the functions and duties`
  line `imposed on it by or under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the Board has persistently made default in complying with any direction issued by the`
  line `Central Government under this Act or in the discharge of the functions and duties imposed on it by or`
  line `under the provisions of this Act and as a result of such default the financial position of the Board or`
  line `the administration of the Board has deteriorated; or`
  line
  line `(c) that circumstances exist which render it necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may, by notification, supersede the Board for such period, not exceeding six`
  line `months, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Board,`
  line
  line `(a) all the members shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `exercised or discharged by or on behalf of the Board, shall until the Board is reconstituted under`
  line `sub-section (3), be exercised and discharged by such person or persons as the Central Government`
  line `may direct; and`
  line
  line `(c) all property owned or controlled by the Board shall, until the Board is reconstituted under`
  line `sub-section (3), vest in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government may reconstitute the Board by a fresh appointment and in such`
  line `case any person or persons who vacated their offices under clause (a) of sub-section (2), shall not be`
  line `deemed disqualified for appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, at any time, before the expiration of the period of`
  line `supersession, take action under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall cause a notification issued under sub-section (1) and a full report of`
  line `any action taken under this section and the circumstances leading to such action to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament at the earliest.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (31463)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 63
  title `Returns and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 10, for sixty days (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31463&sectionno=18&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall furnish to the Central Government at such time and`
  line `in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central Government may direct, such returns and`
  line `statements and such particulars in regard to any proposed or existing programme for the promotion and`
  line `development of the securities market, as the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board shall, within ^1[`
  line `ninety days] after`
  line `the end of each financial year, submit to the Central Government a report in such form, as may be`
  line `prescribed, giving a true and full account of its activities, policy and programmes during the previous`
  line `financial year.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of the report received under sub-section (2) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (31464)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 64
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31464&sectionno=19&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by general or special order in writing delegate to any member,`
  line `officer of the Board or any other person subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the`
  line `order, such of its powers and functions under this Act (except the powers under section 29) as it may`
  line `deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (31465)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 65
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1999, s. 11, for "an order of the Board made" (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31465&sectionno=20&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by ^1`
  line `[an order of the Board made, before the commencement`
  line `of the Securities Laws (Second Amendment) Act, 1999 (32 of 1999)], under this Act, or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder may prefer an appeal to the Central Government within such time as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall be admitted if it is preferred after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor if the`
  line `appellant satisfies the Central Government that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within`
  line `the prescribed period.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal made under this section shall be made in such form and shall be accompanied by a`
  line `copy of the order appealed against and by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The procedure for disposing of an appeal shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that before disposing of an appeal, the appellant shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (31466)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 66
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31466&sectionno=20A&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A. Bar of jurisdiction.--No order passed by the ^2`
  line `[Board or the adjudicating officer] under this`
  line `Act shall be appealable except as provided in ^3`
  line `[section 15T or section 20] and no civil court shall have`
  line `jurisdiction in respect of any matter which the ^2`
  line `[Board or the adjudicating officer] is empowered by, or`
  line `under, this Act to pass any order and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in`
  line `respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any order passed by the ^2`
  line `[Board or the`
  line `adjudicating officer] by, or under, this Act].`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 11 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1999, s. 12, for "Board" (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "section 20" (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (31467)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 67
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31467&sectionno=21&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall exempt any person from any suit or other proceedings which`
  line `might, apart from this Act, be brought against him.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (31468)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 68
  title `Members, officers and employees of the Board to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31468&sectionno=22&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `All members, officers`
  line `and other employees of the Board shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (31469)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 69
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 12 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31469&sectionno=23&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government ^1`
  line `[or Board] or any officer of the Central Government or any member,`
  line `officer or other employee of the Board for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act or the rules or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (31470)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 70
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31470&sectionno=24&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[24. Offences.--(1) Without prejudice to any award of penalty by the adjudicating officer ^2[or the`
  line `Board] under this`
  line `Act, if any person contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets the contravention of the provisions of`
  line `this Act or of any rules or regulations made thereunder, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to ^3`
  line `[ten years, or with fine, which may extend to twenty-five crore rupees or with`
  line both].
  line
  line `(2) If any person fails to pay the penalty imposed by the adjudicating officer ^2[or the`
  line `Board] or fails to comply with`
  line `any ^4*** directions or orders, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than one month but which may extend to ^5`
  line `[ten years, or with fine, which may extend to twenty-five`
  line `crore rupees or with both].`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 13,ibid., for section 24 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 187 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 28, for "one year, or with fine, or with both" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `4. The words "of his" omitted by s. 187,ibid. (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_a:
  sectionId (31471)
  sectionNo 24A
  orderNo 71
  title `Composition of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 29, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31471&sectionno=24A&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_24_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[24A. Composition of certain offences.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence punishable under this Act, not being an offence`
  line `punishable with imprisonment only, or with imprisonment and also with fine, may either before or after`
  line `the institution of any proceeding, be compounded by a Securities Appellate Tribunal or a court before`
  line `which such proceedings are pending.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_b:
  sectionId (31472)
  sectionNo 24B
  orderNo 72
  title `Power to grant immunity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 29, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-10-2002)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31472&sectionno=24B&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_24_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[24B. Power to grant immunity.-- (1) The Central Government may, on recommendation by the`
  line `Board, if the Central Government is satisfied, that any person, who is alleged to have violated any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules or the regulations made thereunder, has made a full and true disclosure`
  line `in respect of the alleged violation, grant to such person, subject to such conditions as it may think fit to impose, immunity from prosecution for any offence under this Act, or the rules or the regulations made`
  line `thereunder or also from the imposition of any penalty under this Act with respect to the alleged violation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such immunity shall be granted by the Central Government in cases where the`
  line `proceedings for the prosecution for any such offence have been instituted before the date of receipt of`
  line `application for grant of such immunity:`
  line
  line `Provided further that recommendation of the Board under this sub-section shall not be binding upon`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section (1) may, at any time, be withdrawn by the`
  line `Central Government, if it is satisfied that such person had, in the course of the proceedings, not complied`
  line `with the condition on which the immunity was granted or had given false evidence, and thereupon such`
  line `person may be tried for the offence with respect to which the immunity was granted or for any other`
  line `offence of which he appears to have been guilty in connection with the contravention and shall also`
  line `become liable to the imposition of any penalty under this Act to which such person would have been`
  line `liable, had not such immunity been granted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (31473)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 73
  title `Exemption from tax on wealth and income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31473&sectionno=25&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Wealth-tax Act, 1957 (27 of 1957), the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) or any other enactment for the`
  line `time being in force relating to tax on wealth, income, profits or gains`
  line
  line `(a) the Board;`
  line
  line `(b) the existing Securities and Exchange Board from the date of its constitution to the date of`
  line `establishment of the Board,`
  line
  line `shall not be liable to pay wealth-tax, income-tax or any other tax in respect of their wealth, income,`
  line `profits or gains derived.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (31474)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 74
  title `Cognizance of offences by courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31474&sectionno=26&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence`
  line `punishable under this Act or any rules or regulations made thereunder, save on a complaint made by the`
  line `Board ^1`
  line ***.
  line ^2
  line *****
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with the previous sanction of the Central Government" omitted by Act 9 of 1995, s. 14 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 27 of 2014, s. 19 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_a:
  sectionId (31475)
  sectionNo 26A
  orderNo 75
  title `Establishment of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31475&sectionno=26A&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[26A. Establishment of Special Courts.--(1) The Central Government may, for the purpose of`
  line `providing speedy trial of offences under this Act, by notification, establish or designate as many Special`
  line `Courts as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court shall consist of a single judge who shall be appointed by the Central Government`
  line `with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court within whose jurisdiction the judge to be`
  line `appointed is working.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a judge of a Special Court unless he is,`
  line `immediately before such appointment, holding the office of a Sessions Judge or an Additional Sessions`
  line `Judge, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_b:
  sectionId (31476)
  sectionNo 26B
  orderNo 76
  title `Offences triable by Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 20 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31476&sectionno=26B&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[26B. Offences triable by Special Courts.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all offences under this Act committed prior to the date of`
  line `commencement of the Securities Laws (Amendment) Act, 2014 (27 of 2014) or on or after the date of`
  line `such commencement, shall be taken cognizance of and tried by the Special Court established for the area`
  line `in which the offence is committed or where there are more Special Courts than one for such area, by such`
  line `one of them as may be specified in this behalf by the High Court concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_c:
  sectionId (31477)
  sectionNo 26C
  orderNo 77
  title `Appeal and revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 20 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31477&sectionno=26C&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_26_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[26C. Appeal and revision.-- The High Court may exercise, so far as may be applicable, all the`
  line `powers conferred by Chapters XXIX and XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) on a`
  line `High Court, as if a Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court were a Court`
  line `of Session trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_d:
  sectionId (31478)
  sectionNo 26D
  orderNo 78
  title `Application of Code to proceedings before Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_d_content
  footnotes `@1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 20 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31478&sectionno=26D&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_26_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[26D. Application of Code to proceedings before Special Court.-- (1) Save as otherwise provided`
  line `in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply to the`
  line `proceedings before a Special Court and for the purposes of the said provisions, the Special Court shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Court of Session and the person conducting prosecution before a Special Court shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Public Prosecutor within the meaning of clause (u) of section 2 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(2) The person conducting prosecution referred to in sub-section (1) should have been in practice as`
  line `an advocate for not less than seven years or should have held a post, for a period of not less than seven`
  line `years, under the Union or a State, requiring special knowledge of law.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_e:
  sectionId (31479)
  sectionNo 26E
  orderNo 79
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 20 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31479&sectionno=26E&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_26_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[26E. Transitional provisions.-- Any offence committed under this Act, which is triable by a Special`
  line `Court shall, until a Special Court is established, be taken cognizance of and tried by a Court of Session`
  line `exercising jurisdiction over the area, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect the powers of the High Court under`
  line `section 407 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) to transfer any case or class of cases`
  line `taken cognizance by a Court of Session under this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (31480)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 80
  title `Contravention by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31480&sectionno=27&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[Contravention by companies].--(1) Where ^2[a contravention of any of the provisions of this Act`
  line `Act or any rule, regulation, direction or order made thereunder] an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the ^3[contravention] was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the ^3[contravention] was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an ^3[contravention] under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the ^3[contravention] has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of the ^3[contravention] and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 188, for marginal heading (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 188, ibid., for "an offence under this Act" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 188, ibid., for "offence" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
