obj_root_law_sections_28_a:
  sectionId (31482)
  sectionNo 28A
  orderNo 82
  title `Recovery of amounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31482&sectionno=28A&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[28A. Recovery of amounts.--(1) If a person fails to pay the penalty imposed ^2[under this Act] or`
  line `fails to comply with any direction of the Board for refund of monies or fails to comply with a direction of`
  line `disgorgement order issued under section 11B or fails to pay any fees due to the Board, the Recovery`
  line `Officer may draw up under his signature a statement in the specified form specifying the amount due`
  line `from the person (such statement being hereafter in this Chapter referred to as certificate) and shall`
  line `proceed to recover from such person the amount specified in the certificate by one or more of the`
  line `following modes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) attachment and sale of the person‘s movable property;`
  line
  line `(b) attachment of the person‘s bank accounts;`
  line
  line `(c) attachment and sale of the person‘s immovable property;`
  line
  line `(d) arrest of the person and his detention in prison;`
  line
  line `(e) appointing a receiver for the management of the person's movable and immovable properties,`
  line
  line `and for this purpose, the provisions of sections 220 to 227, 228A, 229, 232, the Second and Third`
  line `Schedules to the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and the Income-tax (Certificate Proceedings) Rules,`
  line `1962, as in force from time to time, in so far as may be, apply with necessary modifications as if the said`
  line `provisions and the rules made thereunder were the provisions of this Act and referred to the amount due`
  line `under this Act instead of to income-tax under the Income-tax Act, 1961.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, the person's movable or immovable property or`
  line `monies held in bank accounts shall include any property or monies held in bank accounts which has been`
  line `transferred directly or indirectly on or after the date when the amount specified in certificate had become`
  line `due, by the person to his spouse or minor child or son's wife or son's minor child, otherwise than for`
  line `adequate consideration, and which is held by, or stands in the name of, any of the persons aforesaid; and`
  line `so far as the movable or immovable property or monies held in bank accounts so transferred to his minor`
  line `child or his son's minor child is concerned, it shall, even after the date of attainment of majority by such`
  line `minor child or son's minor child, as the case may be, continue to be included in the person's movable or`
  line `immovable property or monies held in bank accounts for recovering any amount due from the person`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--Any reference under the provisions of the Second and Third Schedules to the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and the Income-tax (Certificate Proceedings) Rules, 1962 to the`
  line `assessee shall be construed as a reference to the person specified in the certificate.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.--Any reference to appeal in Chapter XVIID and the Second Schedule to the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), shall be construed as a reference to appeal before the Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal under section 15T of this Act.`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation 4. --The interest referred to in section 220 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 shall`
  line `commence from the date the amount became payable by the person.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Recovery Officer shall be empowered to seek the assistance of the local district`
  line `administration while exercising the powers under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the recovery of`
  line `amounts by a Recovery Officer under sub-section (1), pursuant to non-compliance with any direction`
  line `issued by the Board under section 11B, shall have precedence over any other claim against such person.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of sub-sections (1), (2) and (3), the expression "Recovery Officer‘‘ means any`
  line `officer of the Board who may be authorised, by general or special order in writing, to exercise the powers`
  line `of a Recovery Officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 21 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 189, for "by the adjudicating officer" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `3. The Explanation ins. by Act 21 of 2019, s. 42 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 21-2-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_b:
  sectionId (48992)
  sectionNo 28B
  orderNo 83
  title `Continuance of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 190 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=48992&sectionno=28B&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_28_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[28B. Continuance of proceedings.—(1) Where a person dies, his legal representative shall be liable to pay any sum which the deceased would have been liable to pay, if he had not died, in the like manner and to the same extent as the deceased:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in case of any penalty payable under this Act, a legal representative shall be liable only in case the penalty has been imposed before the death of the deceased person.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1),—`
  line
  line `(a) any proceeding for disgorgement, refund or an action for recovery before the Recovery Officer under this Act, except a proceeding for levy of penalty, initiated against the deceased before his death, shall be deemed to have been initiated against the legal representative, and may be continued against the legal representative from the stage at which it stood on the date of the death of the deceased and all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly;`
  line
  line `(b) any proceeding for disgorgement, refund or an action for recovery before the Recovery Officer under this Act, except a proceeding for levy of penalty, which could have been initiated against the deceased if he had survived, may be initiated against the legal representative and all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Every legal representative shall be personally liable for any sum payable by him in his capacity as legal representative if, while his liability for such sum remains undischarged, he creates a charge on or disposes of or parts with any assets of the estate of the deceased, which are in, or may come into, his possession, but such liability shall be limited to the value of the asset so charged, disposed of or parted with.`
  line
  line `(4) The liability of a legal representative under this section shall be limited to the extent to which the estate of the deceased is capable of meeting the liability.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section “legal representative” means a person who in law represents the estate of a deceased person, and includes any person who intermeddles with the estate of the deceased and where a party sues or is sued in a representative character, the person on whom the estate devolves on the death of the party so suing or sued.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_c:
  sectionId (50879)
  sectionNo 28C
  orderNo 84
  title `Powers of Board not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.`
