obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (31483)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31483&sectionno=29&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office and other conditions of service of the Chairman and the members under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the additional functions that may be performed by the Board under section 11;`
  line
  line ^1*****;
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which the accounts of the Board shall be maintained under section 15;`
  line
  line `^2[(da) the manner of inquiry under sub-section (1) of section 15-I;`
  line
  line `(db) the salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the ^3[`
  line Presiding
  line `Officers, Members] and other officers and employees of the Securities Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `section 15-O and sub-section (3) of section 15S;`
  line
  line `(dc) the procedure for the investigation of misbehaviour or incapacity of the ^4`
  line `Presiding Officers,`
  line `or other Members] of the Securities Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 15Q;`
  line
  line `(dd) the form in which an appeal may be filed before the Securities Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `section 15T and the fees payable in respect of such appeal];`
  line
  line `(e) the form and the manner in which returns and report to be made to the Central Government`
  line `under section 18;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, or in respect of which provision is to`
  line `be, or may be, made by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (c) omitted by Act 9 of 1995, s. 16 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 59 of 2002, s. 31, for "Presiding Officers" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 31, ibid., for "Presiding Officers" (w.e.f. 29-10-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (31484)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 86
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31484&sectionno=30&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, ^1*** by notification, make regulations`
  line `consistent with this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the times and places of meetings of the Board and the procedure to be followed at such`
  line `meetings under sub-section (1) of section 7 including quorum necessary for the transaction of`
  line business;
  line
  line `(b) the term and other conditions of service of officers and employees of the Board under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) the matters relating to issue of capital, transfer of securities and other matters incidental`
  line `thereto and the manner in which such matters shall be disclosed by the companies under section 11A;`
  line
  line `^3[(ca) the utilisation of the amount credited under sub-section (5) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(cb) the fulfilment of other conditions relating to collective investment scheme under`
  line `sub-section (2A) of section 11AA;]`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions subject to which certificate of registration is to be issued, the amount of fee to`
  line `be paid for certificate of registration and the manner of suspension or cancellation of certificate of`
  line `registration under section 12;]`
  line
  line `^4[(da) the terms determined by the Board for settlement of proceedings under sub-section (2) and`
  line `the procedure for conducting of settlement proceedings under sub-section (3) of section 15JB;`
  line
  line `(db) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations or in respect of`
  line `which provision is to be made by regulations.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "with the previous approval of the Central Government" omitted by Act 9 of 1995, s. 17 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 17, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 22 (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-7-2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (31485)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 87
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31485&sectionno=31&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (31486)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 88
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932&sectionId=31486&sectionno=32&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00014_199215_1517807319932
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
